required to match with the results of the CFT. Hence we conclude
that the absorption cross section is not derived from the bulk
scalar propagation in AdS space, but it can be obtained from its
dual CFT correlation function as the scattering matrix
does.

Quasinormal modes 
Even though we encounter some difficulties in calculating the
absorption cross section in the BTZ black hole background, we can
calculate the quasinormal modes. In asymptotically flat space like
in the Schwarzschild black hole, these modes are
usually defined as the solutions which are purely ingoing wave
() at the event horizon and which
purely outgoing () near infinity
(see Fig.5). The initial ingoing wave from infinity is not
allowed.
