 dS absorption cross section 
 Up to now we do not insert
the curvature radius  of dS space. The correct absorption
coefficient can be recovered when replacing  with 
. An absorption coefficient by the cosmological
horizon is defined formally by A  _dS  = 
F  _out (z=1) F  _out (z=0) .
 It is found that there is no absorption of a
scalar wave in  de Sitter space in a semiclassical way. This means
that de Sitter space is usually stable and in thermal equilibrium
with the scalar perturbation, unlike the AdS-black hole. The
cosmological horizon not only absorbs radiation (scalar
perturbaton) but also emits that previously absorbed by itself at
the same rate, keeping the curvature radius  of de Sitter space
fixed. It can be proved by the relation of 
 and 
. This picture coincides with the plane wave
propagation of the energy  under the potential step with
 which shows the classical picture of what the particle
goes on, as is shown in Sec. II-A.


